                    <statement>
                        <p>
                            Let's make more precise the difference between three vectors whose span is a plan and three
                            vectors whose span is <m>\R^3</m>.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Let's compare <m> \vvec_1 = \threevec220,~~~
	    \vvec_2 = \threevec11{-1},~~~
	    \vvec_3 = \threevec{-1}01</m> and <m>\wvec_1 = \threevec220,~~~
	    \wvec_2 = \threevec11{-1},~~~
	    \wvec_3 = \threevec{-5}{-5}{1}</m>.
                        </p>
                    </statement>
                    <solution>
                        <p>
                            See <url href="https://understandinglinearalgebra.org/sec-linear-dep.html#example-span-r3">Example 2.4.1</url>
                            and <url href="https://understandinglinearalgebra.org/sec-linear-dep.html#example-span-plane">Example 2.4.2 </url>.
                        </p>
                    </solution>
                    
                </exercise>
            </page>
